participating-org.narrative:
The NGO called Women Actions and Development (FAD) was created in the Republic of Niger between the adherents to the existing statutes elaborated in accordance with the spirit of the ordinance n° 84-06 of the 1st March 1984 bearing the regime of the associations,modified and completed by Law N ° 91-006 of May 20, 1991. It is apolitical, democratic, no religious and no-profit affiliation.
TheNGO FAD aims at promoting, protecting, assisting, supporting, recognizing the rights and duties of women in Niger through sustainable development and proximity actions including:
- Creating a " host house" for women in social difficulties with or homeless women.
- through any material and financial help to rural women.
- By all other actions decided in advanced in General Assembly;

To this end, it sets its specific objectives as:
- fight against all forms of discrimination against women;
- to combat violence against women and children in all its forms;
- strengthen the promotion of women and the protectionof the child;
- fight against inequality and inequity related to gender;
- contribute to the improvement of living conditions for women and children#s welfare;
- to contribute to the development of youth and the promotion of culture;
- strengthen girl#s schooling;
- contribute to the implementation of the Convention on the Rights of Women (CRW) and the Convention on the Rights of the Child (CRC);
- Participate actively in the development, implementation, monitoring and evaluation of United Nations system programs in Niger;
- Contribute to the implementation of the International Commission for Development (ICPD) Action programs, the Millennium Development Goals (MDGs), the New Partnership for Africa's Development (NEPAD) and the Program Strengthening of Adolescent and Youth sexual health including the prevention of STD / HIV /AIDS (sexual violence, ignorance, harmful traditional practices etc ...);
- mobilize resources for sexual and reproductive health on one hand and promote family planning on the other.
